To retrieve and delete a CSV file in a SpringBoot application, we can modify the existing FileCopyService class as follows:

1. For Retrieval:

@Service
public class FileCopyService {
    
    @Value("${file.source}")
    private String sourceFilePath;
    
    public List<String[]> retrieveFile() throws IOException {
        List<String[]> data = new ArrayList<>();
        try (CSVReader reader = new CSVReader(new FileReader(sourceFilePath))) {
            String[] line;
            while ((line = reader.readNext()) != null) {
                data.add(line);
            }
        }
        return data;
    }
}


This code will read the CSV file from the source location and return the data as a List of String arrays.

2. For Deletion:

@Service
public class FileCopyService {
    
    @Value("${file.source}")
    private String sourceFilePath;
    
    public void deleteFile() throws IOException {
        Files.deleteIfExists(Paths.get(sourceFilePath));
    }
}


This code will delete the CSV file from the source location if it exists. 

Note: In both cases, we are using the sourceFilePath property to specify the location of the CSV file. You can modify this property in the application.yml file to change the file location.